    "analysis": "The previous Executor run aggregated metric and trace series by (cmdb_id, kpi_name) and (cmdb_id, trace_name) and returned compact summaries (count, mean, P95, min_ts, max_ts). From those results: multiple OS and DB metric groups exist (most have 30–31 samples covering 2020-04-11 00:00 to ~00:29/00:30 Asia/Shanghai timezone). Trace groups are dominated by docker_001 (30 samples) and include several remoteprocess and jdbc/span metrics. Notable signals to inspect further: trace.from_os_022.remoteprocess.* (high mean/p95), and various os_* network and disk KPIs. We have not yet performed anomaly detection within the incident window using the computed global thresholds. Next step is to compute global thresholds (P95) per group using the full series (already computed in summary step) and then detect anomalies inside the incident time window (2020-04-11 00:00 to 00:30 Asia/Shanghai) to identify which component-KPI groups have anomalous consecutive points. Return compact aggregates only so we can narrow candidates for deeper fault identification.",
